<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>DFLib - Hockey Player Stats Charts</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Data visualization with DFLib DataFrame - generated charts and dashboards based on NHL player statistics">
    <meta name="keywords" content="DFLib Chars, dashboards, visualizations, Apache ECharts, hockey stats">

    <script type='text/javascript' src='{{{echartsUrl}}}'></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Mono:wght@400;700&amp;display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
<style>
body { font-family: "Roboto Mono",sans-serif;font-size: 12px;}
h1 { font-family: "Roboto Mono",sans-serif;font-size: 30px;font-weight: 700;}
h2 { font-family: "Roboto Mono",sans-serif;font-size: 18px;font-weight: 600;}
.chart_legend { margin: 50px auto; width: 1000px; position: relative;} 
.dfl_ech { margin: 50px auto; padding: 20px;border: 1px solid #ddd;border-radius: 8px; }

</style>

<div class="chart_legend"> 
    <h1>Hockey Player Stats</h1>
    <p>Generated by <a href="/">DFLib</a>.</p>
    <h2>Top Skaters Points</h2>
    The data is for the 2023-24 regular season. Points are (goals+assists). Assists are turned off by default, click on "assists" label to show the values.
</div>
{{{chartDiv0}}}
<script type='text/javascript'>{{{chartScript0}}}</script>

<div class="chart_legend"> 
    <h2>Player Weight - Historical Trends</h2>
X axis is the year when a player started playing at the NHL, Y - his last recorded weight. Recent data may be skewed, as the age of the active players is lower on average vs retired players.
</div>
{{{chartDiv1}}}
<script type='text/javascript'>{{{chartScript1}}}</script>
</body>
</html>